Reasoning: The paper discusses the comparison of QoS parameters of SIP protocol in two different wireless LAN standards, 802.11a and 802.11b. This involves the study of network performance, packet drops, and end-to-end delay, which are all related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of comparative plots, which suggests the involvement of multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the study involves the analysis of security and privacy issues, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Lastly, the study involves the analysis of communication environments, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
